headline: Lululemon Faces Proxy Fight As Quality Concerns Weigh On Valuation
summary: Founder Chip Wilson has launched a proxy fight targeting lululemon athletica’s board following a recent high profile leggings recall tied to quality complaints. Wilson is pushing to replace certain directors and publicly challenging the company’s quality control and overall direction. The campaign coincides with CEO Calvin McDonald’s pending departure, raising questions about future leadership and governance.
